s</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>103 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 10th 11:33 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.27]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello i am currently a lvl 40 iksar necro and i am finding it rather time consuming at the moment so i thought maybe others have had hard times in hell and maybe could use my advice or could offer some other so here goes.  currently for exp i fight the dwarves in BB.  my favorite camp is den and tagnis on the shore near the druid ring.  they are both blue, provide ok exp at 40, are static non roaming spawns (i hate hunting for mobs in ot) and drop weapons for my pet and up to 5pp.  den is on kaladim citizens faction and tagnis is on guard faction but i am hated anyway so i dont really care.  i highly recomend this spot as it is not camped alot, atleast on TT.  <br><br>When i get too bored i head over to Soluseks Eye and do the singe kindle camp.  if u go to eq maps here you can see how to get to the kindle camp.  on the way there you pass by a kind of ramp room right near the kindle spawn.  this is actually where singe spawns, not 6 on the map.  is really a very easy camp at 40.  Jobeker kills the gobos very easily.  the imp skin gloves sell well, the obsidian bead hoop is an ok caster ear if u dont have batskulls, the belt from singe is good for melees and casters on naggy raids, and the ring is pretty crappy but is ok for your monk u have sitting on the account taking up space.  really a safe camp and the gloves are worth the time it takes.  well just a suggestion.<br>&nbsp;<br>Fendrish 48 Barb War<br>Deadinc 38 Iksar Necro<br>Zebriz 12 Iksar Shaman</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
