<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101060817619959></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101060817619959><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101060817619959>Crazy Crazy Dark Elves</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101060817619959#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2903><span id= >The Honorable DaKineNugs</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>103 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 9th 3:29 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.28]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>you all must not be 34 yet.  call of bones takes off 12 hp.  i have a 40 necro now(nm the 38 in the sig) and he has a WHOPPING 778 hp.  now i am not twinked, and i have a 175 int that i worked damn hard to get.  and that hp readout is with greater shielding and a couple of hp items.  <br>i kill a mob, when im done i have about 60-70m i cob till fm then regen.  if i didnt have regen i would have to either tap or vc when i was done medding.  vc takes 144mana and heals 200hp. drain spirit takes 189 mana and heals 209.  so now as a Dark Elf you have to either spend the extra mana to heal yourself on top of the mana required to dot and fear kite the mob, or you have to spend extra time medding/healing. and if u decided to heal yourself then u have to spend time medding up after the fight from 40-50 as the heal spells will take some mana out of u.  and if any one has used either of those spells you know that vc does not hurt the mob, as it does the damage over time, and taps are mana expensive and slow. <br>And even more so as you progress int the dark arts your mana disease grows in the amount used.  Lich at 49 does 30 hp to the caster. at lvl 60 iksar regen is at 18hps. this is just like what you inkies get with cob.  except us iksar get alot more mana with lich. AND demi lich at 60 does 48 hp dmg.  how in the world a DE necro could use that spell and keep it on for more than like 5 ticks is beyond me. <br>As far as int goes as of lvl 34 a necro can quite easily go to sk to hunt treants or many other places to go get money for int items.  and the sheer number of int items availabe in ec today has forced the prices on most non uber ones into the affordable catagory allowing for us iksar to get to a respectable int level very quickly.<br>As far as night vision goes, iksar may not get infravision, but they get night vision, the harvester has effect: deadeye which has night vision and call of bones gives infravision too.  so vision is NOT a problem to any necro and if u choose a de for that reason you need help.  <br>In fact if u choose a de period you need help, (hears the flames lighting) there is really no reason to make a de necro as far as i can see. If you want to go the route of getting as large a mana pool as possible, make an erudite.  If u want to level quickly (well faster than other necros) be an iksar.  If u want to be original be a gnome or a human(course there are not a TON of iksar necros yet).  If u want to be the most played out, obvious and really have nothin going for you other than blue skin and infravision, be a Dark Elf.....O YA they look crappy too, only the plate and chain wearing DE's look good. well ive vented now =) go ahead light me up, i dare you inkies.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan 10 11:19:31 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Fendrish 48 Barb War<br>Deadinc 38 Iksar Necro<br>Zebriz 12 Iksar Shaman</td></tr>
