	   <tr><td colspan=2><span style='color: green;'><br>Hey.<br><br>Iksar necromancers can indeed do the Epic weapon quest.  However, as Cannis quite rightly said, you're a long way from being ready to do it.  <br><br>You're going to need items from three of the planes:<br><LI>Cloak of Spiroc Feathers - PoA<br><LI>Eye of Innoruuk - PoH<br><LI>Blood of Cazic Thule - PoF<br><br>Since you have to be L46, or above just to enter the planes, it'll be a while before you can even get close to these items.  If you follow <b><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=762&amp;mid=10028584197315 target=_new>this link</a></b> you can see a brief description of what you have to do for the quest.<br><br>What the synopsis <b>doesn't</b> say, but which I remember reading <i>somewhere</i> is that you need allied faction in Freeport.<br><br>The only other issue you need to bear in mind, is that the Scythe of Shadowed Soul isn't particularly useful to anyone other than the necromancer.  (As oppossed to, say for example, the Cleric epic, which gives a manaless ressurection.)  So, it may be a bit trickier to get people to help you with the quest.<br><br>I don't think using invis would work, because being invis has funny effects on the way NPCs react to you.  (Try talking to an NPC while invis.  They just won't speak to you.  I don't know, but I'd be wary of this.  (Considering the difficulty in getting the items you'll be handing over...))<br><br>Using feign death <b>might</b> be more successful, since I know some monks have used this for banking and questing.  However, you might want to check whether you'll survive long enough to actually FD, without being killed.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Good luck on your journeys, broodling.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br></span style='color: green;'><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jan  9 06:06:40 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
