<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101057675411885></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101057675411885><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101057675411885>RE: INT Items</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101057675411885#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Sage>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>111 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 9th 6:45 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.39]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><span style='color: green;'><br>Hey.<br><br>First thing:<br>At lower levels, INT isn't actually as useful as most people seem to think.  (<i>This <b>may</b> not be exactly accurate, but it'll give you a reasonable idea.</i>)  You get one point of mana for every five points of INT, per level.<br><br>Or:<br><br>Mana = (Lvl x INT) / 5<br><br>So, at L8, you get a little more than 1 1/2 mana per point of INT.  On the other hand, at L45, you'll get 9 mana per INT.  Hopefully, you can see pretty clearly that INT at low levels is a bit over-rated.<br><br>What you might want to look int, are +mana and +HP items.  One of my favourites is the <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=786 target=_new><b>Gold Jaded Bracelet</b></a>.  This gives you +15HP and +15 mana.  These go for about 30PP each, or 50PP for a pair.  A comparable item is a <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=776 target=_new><b>Bracelet of Woven Grass</b></a>.  This gives +3INT and +12HP and sells for close to 100PP.  However, you're getting more mana from the Gold Jaded Bracelet, until around L25.  (And you'll be getting more HP and Ac too!)<br><br>Also, as a couple of other people have stated, 200INT isn't exactly vital.  (My necromancer is currently L44 and I have only 157 INT.  I got to around L30, before I had many items with +INT.  (I was wearing practically a full set of cured silk!))  More INT might be nice, but you can get by without it.  Remember, DoTs and fear kiting are among the most mana efficient means of killing possible.<br><br>If you are determined to boost your INT, you may also want to consider these items:<br><LI><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4709 target=_new><b>Imbued Platinum Amber Ring</b></a><br><LI><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4708 target=_new><b>Imbued Golden Amber Earring</b></a><br>Both of these items are relatively cheap, because the imbued amber is cheap and of use only to followers of Cazic Thule.  You can get them cheap, by doing all the running around yourself.  Buy the amber and metal from a jeweller.  If you ask nicely, a shaman can enchant the amber.  And a jeweller will probably do the combine <b>very</b> cheaply.  (Look for a master jeweller.  You don't wanna risk losing your components.)<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br></span style='color: green;'><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
