	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm dying to play a necromancer and I'm torn between iksar and erudite.  I have one of each, the iksar at 8 and the erudite at 6.  Still deciding which to stick with.  <br><br>I love the look of dark elf necros, especially the females (yum) but there are too many.  Gnome was tempting, but my main is a 40 dwarf cleric so I wasn't interested in a short race.  The bald human look may be the best of any necromancer appearances but if I'm going to start with that low intelligence, I want to go with the iksar.  <br><br>This is my humble take on the advantages and disadvantages of erudites and iksars.  I'm writing this more for my own benefit, but thought others might find it interesting.<br><br>Erudite - Great intelligence, great newbie zone for first few levels.  With the luclin portals I was able to load up on bone chips and port over to dreadlands for free, made a ton selling to high level necs.  A ton for a non-twink anyway.  Erudites also get to wear flayed armor which just sounds cool.  I'm also dying to get a harvester, which would benefit an erudite much more than an iksar I think because of deadeye and the relatively low intelligence on the harvester. Oh yeah, +5 magic resist too.<br><br>Iksar - 4 big things going for them.  1. Regen - love the idea of regen along with the mana-health conversion spells.  2. Great starting areas for xp - unfortunately, my iksar is quite broke, can only afford 2 8th level spells so far.  3. Looks - Scaled death or conehead nec?  Easy choice there though I think I have my erudites beard and hair camoflauging the cone pretty well.  4. Unique - Even compared to erudites, there were 2 iksar necs on my server last night compared to 8 erudites.  <br><br>Just my thoughts, have not decided which way I'm going yet.  Now I just have to talk my wife into playing with her beastlord as I think nec and beastlord would be an awesome combo )<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
