	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thanks for your post Necrosrule... you make some important points I really wanted to pound on here.<br><br>My Necro is 37, but I have a level 50 Ranger.  Through regular grouping with the Ranger I've found two things.  First, people don't like to group with Necros (or are simply indifferent to it) and secondly, easily HALF the necros I group with don't know HOW to group effectively.  Therefore it becomes a vicious cycle and people continue to not appreciate the necros in their group.<br><br>Let me say this to anyone who is a Necro that groups... Fear kiting in a group should be a group decision.  PLEASE DON'T FEAR UNLESS you have no healer!  As a Ranger/puller, I've usually gone to a lot of trouble to run off and BRING the mob to the group.  Having to chase it around while it's Feared is a serious pain in the arse.  Several times grouping in DL with necros -- they always insist on Fearing and this is ridiculous.<br><br>Next, if you enter a group and there is no Chanter, you should mem Screaming Terror immediately.  My necro grouped with another in OT and the other necro said, &quot;You USE that spell?!&quot;  HELL YES!  Half the time I use it and the tanks look at me after a battle with an add and say, &quot;What class are you again?&quot;  It doesn't last very long, true, but it can be recast and can keep the add from agroing the healer or pounding a tank into pulp.<br><br>Many Necros shrug at being in a group -- &quot;They just want me to dump my mana into the healer.&quot;  My advice is to get creative with what you've got.  Sometime the mobs are dropping so fast there's no time to cast a DoT... but other times that's not so at all.  Places like DL and KC, the battle can drag on, and our powerful DoT's can speed up the experience DRAMATICALLY.  Even in OT, I'm casting Venom before the mob has even reached the other tanks.  Makes a huge difference in battle.<br><br>Keep spreading the good word!  Necros rock in groups, but we DO have to adapt to whatever we're grouped with and mem different spells accordingly.<br><br>Sytox<br>Terris-Thule Server  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
