	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 10th 7:49 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.37]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As an Iksar necromancer, We would have to say We are quite superior to humans.  Though everyone esle seems to be underplaying the regen factor of the Iksar, I find it VERY IMPORTANT.  High Intelligence is well and good, and since Iksar and Humans start out with the same int, it's moot.  However, the Iksar, in Our experience, has a much higher manna/survival ratio simply for the fact of our racial regen.  Another point, though perhaps quite minor, is that We get forage, allowing us to travel quite far if necessary, and reducing Our dependence on others for food.<br><br>Yes, We are hated by all other races.  Big Deal.  We are necromancers, and that choice is not one to be made if you wish to be loved by the masses.  If you're looking for love, be a chanter.  Besides, from a leveling perspective, there is really no reason to ever even leave Kunark, ever (though We tend to find elf hunting a pleasant pasttime).<br><br>Heh, have the paladin convince you that humans and Iksar are equals if you wish.. personally, I would rather munch on some pickles.<br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane-Infection<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
